The paper deals with network analysis, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of machine learning, specifically convolutional neural networks, suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves computational methods for dealing with large amounts of data, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of graphlet count in bioinformatics suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of machine learning for estimating graphlet count suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
